article.headline: New Hampshire 49, Dartmouth 20
article.story:
DURHAM, N.H. (AP) -- Ricky Santos threw for 267 yards and rushed
for 48 more to lead New Hampshire to a 49-20 lead over Dartmouth on
Saturday.

Trailing 10-7 midway through the first quarter, New Hampshire
(3-0) closed the first half with 28 straight points to build a
35-10 halftime lead.

Santos began the spurt with a 1-yard touchdown run that gave the
Wildcats the lead for good in the first quarter. Santos also threw
one of his three TD passes, extending the lead to 21-10 in the
second quarter.

On the opening kick of the second half, New Hampshire's Etienne
Boulay forced a fumble that was recovered by teammate Corey Graham.
Three plays later, Keith LeVan scored on a 7-yard run to give New
Hampshire a 42-10 lead 50 seconds into the third quarter.

Brett Lowe closed the scoring with a 3-yard TD reception from
Joshua Cohen at 4:12.

Charlie Rittgers was 16 of 25 for 166 yards and one touchdown
pass for Dartmouth (1-1).
